results.title: The Thunder God and the Bi-Beast
A Day in the Death of Darkoth!
Like a Bat Out of Heaven
Doom!
results.description: Nick Fury asks Thor's aid in investigating an alien ship heading for earth; Thor arrives and triggers the awakening of an alien protector, Bet Ray Bill; Bill bests Thor and takes up his hammer only to be accidentally summoned to Asgard by Odin who thinks he is summoning Thor.

results.title: A Fool and His Hammer
results.description: Bill and Thor fight in single combat for the honor of weilding Mjolner and the alien bests the god of thunder.

results.title: Something Old, Something New
results.description: Odin has the dwarves create a hammer for Bill and sends the alien and his son into space to rescue Bill's people.

results.title: Carlin and Simonson's Page O' Thor Stuff
Though Hel Should Bar the Way
results.description: Thor, Sif and Bill save the latters people from alien demons; Odin gives Bill a civilian identity when he strikes his hammer on the ground.

results.title: The Past Is a Bucket of Ashes
results.description: Thor loses the Don Blake identity and gains secret i.d. of Sigurd Jarlson courtesy of Nick Fury (his disguise being, you guessed it, a pair of glasses); Sigurd gets a job as a construction worker but the site is wrecked by Fafnir looking for the god of thunder.

results.title: [The Last Viking]
results.description: Thor is called to an old viking village in the arctic wastes where an old viking, last of his people, tries to trick the thunder god into killing him so he can enter Valhalla.

results.title: If I Should Die Before I Wake
results.description: Eilif is granted strength by Odin so he can assist Thor in fighting Fafnir.

results.title: Whatever Happened To Balder the Brave?
results.description: Balder is sent by Odin to make the perilous journey to Loki's realm to ask the god of mischief for aid in combating an ancient evil; Malekith makes it there first and sways Loki to his side; Balder, forced to break his vow of non-violence by a taunting Loki, cuts off the schemer's head and wanders into teh desert to die.

results.title: That Was No Lady
results.description: Lorelei continues her seduction of Thor; Malekith and the Dark Elves try to capture the Casket of Ancient Winters from its keeper, but the Casket is passed on to his son for protection.

results.title: The Wild Hunt
results.description: The Dark Elves try to capture the Casket of Ancient Winters from its new guardian, Roger Willis; Thor helps out; Malekith captures Thor's true (or at least enchanting) lover, Melodi, and threatens to kill her if the Casket is not given up.

results.title: Into the Realm of Faerie
results.description: Thor and Roger invade the realm of Faerie to rescue Thor's love while keeping the Casket of Ancient Winters out of Malekith's hands; They don't quite succeed; Balder has a chat with a Norn; Odin prepares for battle; Surtur prepares to invade earth.

results.title: The Dark and the Light
results.description: Thor and Roger save Lorelei, but fail to keep Malekith from opening the Casket of Ancient Winters; The Norns convince Balder that life is better than death; Surtur begins his advance.
